                           "Parties undertake that they shall refrain from maligning each other in public, on public forums, or on social media platforms and further undertake to keep the result, orders, and judgments passed by the tribunal confidential.",
                           "Source: visit_visa_entire_agreement.php",
                           "Entire Agreement This Agreement, including Annexure A, website terms and conditions, and management policies as and when updated constitutes the entire agreement between the parties concerning the subject matter and supersedes all prior discussions and agreements. No amendments or modifications to this Agreement shall be effective unless in writing and signed by both parties.",
                           "Source: visit_visa_execution.php",
                           "Execution",
                           "By signing below, both parties acknowledge and agree to the terms and conditions of this Agreement.",
                           "Source: en_annexure_b",
                           "Source: b_intro.php",
                           "Annexure B Refund Policy This Refund Policy (\"Annexure\") is part of the Agreement entered into between DM CONSULTANTS and the Client {{clientName}} . This Annexure outlines the conditions under which the Client may or may not be entitled to a refund for the services provided by DM CONSULTANTS.",
                           "Source: non_refundable_circumstances.php",
                           "NON-REFUNDABLE CIRCUMSTANCES The Client acknowledges and agrees that under no circumstances will DM CONSULTANTS issue a refund if any of the following situations arise:",
                           "Changes in Immigration Laws If any unexpected, subsequent, or retroactive changes to immigration laws or policies occur after the signing of the Agreement, DM CONSULTANTS shall not be held liable for refunding any fees paid, as services were rendered in good faith, based on the prevailing laws at the time-of-service provision.",
                           "Visa Approval Process Visa approval is solely at the discretion of the relevant immigration authorities. DM CONSULTANTS does not guarantee the approval of a visa application. In the event that the visa is rejected by the immigration authorities, DM CONSULTANTS shall not be responsible for issuing any refunds.",
                           "Ambiguity Between Countries If any political or diplomatic issues arise between the country of residence of the Client and the country they are applying to for a Work Permit, DM CONSULTANTS shall not be liable for any refunds.",
                           "Client Withdrawal Before Processing Completion If the Client withdraws their application prior to the completion of the processing services, DM CONSULTANTS shall not be liable for any refund of the fees paid for services already rendered up until the point of withdrawal.",
                           "Inconsistent or Contradictory Information Should the Client provide inconsistent, contradictory, or false information during the application process, which causes the Client to become ineligible for immigration after services have been initiated, no refund will be granted.",
                           "Closure of Immigration Program or Reaching Maximum Capacity If the immigration program in question is closed, or if the maximum capacity for applications is reached, DM CONSULTANTS will make reasonable efforts to find a suitable alternative. However, the Client shall bear any additional costs incurred in the process, and no refunds will be issued. If client refuses to accept the alternate given to change the country/ employer and the client does not agree to the time frame and the terms and conditions , no refunds will be issued.",
                           "Failure to Provide Required Documents In cases where the Client fails to provide the necessary documents within the time frame specified by DM CONSULTANTS or the relevant assessing body, no refund shall be issued.",
                           "Failure to Complete the Immigration Process If the Client fails to attend an interview, neglects to undergo a medical examination, or in any other way does not complete the immigration process, DM CONSULTANTS shall not be responsible for issuing any refund.",
                           "Rejection Due to Medical, Criminal, National Security, Financial Issues and Doubt in Intent of travel.",
                           "If the Client’s application is rejected on grounds related to medical conditions, criminal records, national security concerns, or financial ineligibility, DM CONSULTANTS shall not issue any refund.",
                           "Direct Communication with Authorities If the Client communicates directly with government bodies, immigration authorities, or any other organizations or agents or employers without the written consent of DM CONSULTANTS, and such communication results in a negative impact on the application process, DM CONSULTANTS shall not be liable to provide any refund.",
                           "Provision of False or Fraudulent Information If the Client is found to have provided false, misleading, or fraudulent documents or engaged in any form of misrepresentation or fraud, DM CONSULTANTS shall not issue any refund.",
                           "Completion of Initial Consultation and Document Checklist Once the Client’s file has been created, the initial consultation has been completed, and the Client has received the required document checklist, the Client agrees that the initial payment is non-refundable, as considerable work has already been invested in processing the Client’s file.",
                           "Withdrawal After Agreement Signed If the Client signs the Agreement and then decides not to proceed with the immigration application for any reason, DM CONSULTANTS will not refund any fees paid up to that point.",
                           "Dormancy of Client’s File for 90 Days If the Client\u0027s file is dormant for a period of 90 days or more, during which no communication or action is taken by the Client, DM CONSULTANTS reserves the right to close the application temporarily. In such cases, no refund will be applicable.",
                           "Client Fails to Complete All Required Procedures If the Client fails to complete any necessary procedures, steps, or requirements within the time frame stipulated by DM CONSULTANTS or the immigration authorities (such as medical examinations, interviews, etc.), no refund will be granted.",
                           "No Responsibility for Appointment Scheduling DM CONSULTANTS will not be liable for securing appointment dates with immigration authorities or for any embassy appointment processes. As these actions are outside of DM CONSULTANTS\u0027 control, no refund will be issued if the Client is unable to secure an appointment.",
                           "Visa Rejection After Work Permit Approval Should the Client secure Work Permit approval but subsequently fail to obtain an embassy appointment or face visa rejection due to the employer\u0027s inability to meet verification requirements, work permit getting delayed due to employer or government, or change in the employer legal compliances mandate by the government the Client will not be entitled to get a refund of any amounts paid for previous stages.",
                           "Source: refundable_circumstances.php",
                           "REFUNDABLE CIRCUMSTANCES Refunds will be considered and may be applicable under the following conditions, subject to the terms and conditions set out in this section:",
                           "Full Package Refund Refunds are only applicable if the Client has paid the full package amount as described in Annexure A (Clause 3) of the Agreement. The refund will be processed subject to the stages outlined and the applicable conditions mentioned in this section.",
